# Run operations yourself

When this project needs any of the following, **run the commands yourself** in the workspace. Do not tell the user to restart, migrate, or seed—do it.

## When to run what

- **Schema or enum changes (Prisma)**  
  - `npx prisma migrate deploy` (or create migration if needed)  
  - `npx prisma generate`  
  - If processes lock the client: stop backend (and Prisma Studio if needed) by killing the PID on port 3000 / 5556, then run `npx prisma generate`, then start backend (and Prisma Studio if desired) again.

- **Seed data or seed logic changed**  
  - `npx prisma db seed`

- **Backend .env or code changed (rate limit, env flags, etc.)**  
  - Stop the process on port 3000 (e.g. `taskkill /PID <pid> /F` after `netstat -ano | findstr ":3000"`), then start again: `npx nx serve backend-api` (in background if appropriate).

- **Mobile app code changed**  
  - You cannot restart the app on the user’s device. Tell them to reload (Expo: shake → Reload) only when the change is in the app and they need to pick it up.

## Commands to run (Windows / PowerShell)

- Find PID: `netstat -ano | findstr ":3000"` or `:5556`
- Stop: `taskkill /PID <pid> /F`
- Migrate: `cd c:\Users\asaf0\smart-dooh; npx prisma migrate deploy`
- Generate: `cd c:\Users\asaf0\smart-dooh; npx prisma generate`
- Seed: `cd c:\Users\asaf0\smart-dooh; npx prisma db seed`
- Start backend: `cd c:\Users\asaf0\smart-dooh; npx nx serve backend-api` (use `is_background: true` for long-running)
- Start Prisma Studio: `cd c:\Users\asaf0\smart-dooh; npx prisma studio` (use `is_background: true`)

Run these in the project root (`c:\Users\asaf0\smart-dooh`). Use `;` in PowerShell to chain commands if needed.
